Author:
Vol / Page:  3
Edition:
Quote:  [The beach (Wellington)], A person calling himself Captain Richards, of the schooner

Cheerful, has beguiled and smuggled from the [Wellington] beach, four to five young females to carry with him to the Chatham Islands, to locate them ... amongst the reckless set who form the members of a whaling gang ...
Notes:  1841 Mar 6 NZ Gazette and Spectator (Wellington) 3 quoted in 1982 Richards Whaling and Sealing in the Chatham Islands 22

Date:  27/8/1850
Source:  Letters
Author:  GODLEY
Vol / Page:  94
Edition:  1951
Quote:  What is called `the Beach'; that is the long [Wellington] street (about a mile and a half) if street it can be called, that has houses only on one side and runs along by the sea.
Notes:  1850 Aug 27 Godley Letters (1951) 94



